labor_categories.labor_category: Leadership and Team Coach - Executive Level

raw_data.title: Leadership and Team Coach - Executive Level
raw_data.description: ICF MCC or PCC certified (or equivalent globally) executive coach for senior leaders. Most of these coaches have been leaders in government or corporate and bring extensive experience and credibility to coach executive level leaders. These coaches understand the challenges of senior leaders and the leadership and team competencies expected of them. They can incorpate any client culture, leadership values, and core competencies provided to help the leader achieve their coaching goals. These coaches can implement and debrief leadership assessments as required. Churchill offers a suite of assessments (extra cost) including 360s, EQi, DISC, MBTI, Hogan, Insights Discovery, Team Diagnostic, Clifton Strengths, Enneagram, and more. Each coaching session moves the client forward towards his/her goals and overcoming their challenges through coaching expertise, consistent support and empowering the client to discover new insight, decisions and ways forward. Homework/action learning is often assigned. These coaches can measure success using Churchill's 4 step methodoloy including our Coaching ROI tool. This level of executive coach includes certified "Systemic Team Coaches" for executive team development. Plus certified “Coaching Supervisors” and "Mentor Coaches" used to lead Churchill's ICF coaching certification programs and continuing coach education. Coaching can be delivered in person or Zoom/teams. In person may add travel fees. Coaching can be purchased as specific engagment lengths or coaching-on-demand. Our Optify Coaching Platform can be used.

They educate and empower senior leaders and teams by shifting leadership/team mindsets, changing behavior and building confidence and skills to apply the learnings on the job. They also customize, plan and facilitate retreats and off-sites for strategic planning, organizational change etc. Services can be delivered in person or using Teams/Zoom.  In person may add travel fees.Churchill provides a catalog of off-the-shelf leadership and team development workshops that allow for minor customization or we offer fully customized workshops to meet the client's needs. We can measure success using our 4 steps methodology.

raw_data.description: As Administrators they are responsible for developing and editing reports, and other documents in support of a client’s contracted requirements.  Interfacing with personnel to coordinate logistics, meetings, maintain logs, records and files, distributes assessments, provides end-user support, and performs general administrative duties.  As Graphic Designers they may design, edit and/or finalize Churchill project materials.  As VIrtual Producers they partner with a coach(s) orfacilitator(s) to ensure the smooth running of virtual meetings ie Teams and Zoom.
